@node Bugs "Bugs"
@next Acknowledgements
@prev Author
@toc  Main

				   @{b}Bugs@{ub}
				   @{b}~~~~@{ub}

    I haven't found any bugs in @{b}Address@{ub} so hopefully there aren't any, but
    I'm sorry to say I have yet to see a completely error-free computer
    program. Please report to @{"me" link Author} any bugs you find and I will fix them as
    soon as I can.

    Since I have only tested @{b}Address@{ub} in my particular environment - consist-
    ing of an Amiga 1200, AmigaOS 3.1, a Blizzard 1230-IV, 16 MB FAST RAM, 
    2 MB CHIP RAM, a HP LaserJet 5L, and some other stuff - I have no know-
    ledge whatsoever as to how it would work - or not work - under other 
    configurations. It would be great if you could tell me what your con-
    figuration is and how @{b}Address@{ub} works in your system in the e-mail you 
    are sending to me when you have decided that you want to use the program 
    for the remaining of your days on this Earth. Thus I can include this
    particular environment in the documentation of the next version of 
    @{b}Address@{ub} as one that the program is guaranteed to work in.

    If you have any suggestions as to how I can make @{b}Address@{ub} even better
    a program, don't be afraid to share also these with @{"me" link Author}. I have only
    so much imagination. :-)

@endnode

